article.headline: Robert Morris 74, Wagner 52
article.story: CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- Tony Lee and A.J. Jackson scored 15 points apiece to lead Robert Morris to a 74-52 victory over Wagner and the Colonials' 11th straight win in a battle of Northeast Conference co-leaders Saturday. Robert Morris (23-6, 14-2 Northeast Conference), which moved into first place in the conference for the first time this season, closed the game with an 18-0 run and held Wagner to just four points over the final 8:18. Bateko Francisco added 13 points and Jimmy Langhurst, Jeremy Chappell and Mezie Nwigwe each had 10 for Robert Morris. Lee also added eight assists. The Colonials trailed by as many as 13 points in the first half and were behind 35-28 at the half. Durell Vinson had 16 points and 15 rebounds to lead Wagner (20-7, 13-3), which had won three in a row and dropped into a second-place tie with Sacred Heart with two regular-season games remaining.
